our money-removing attempts to fail from the start--if the player characters take some action. Turn your attempts into adventures. If a thief robs the player character's castle, be ready with an adventure where the character can try to track him down. In fact, he may even catch the thief, but only after the scoundrel has squandered the character's fortune!\000\000S\000\000\000\033\000\000\000\357\007\020\000\211\012\020\0008\000\000\000 @\2006\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\202\202\343*\352$\334\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000\000\000\000\000Table of Contents\000\000 \000\000e\000\000\0004\000\000\0006\012\020\000\356\012\020\0001\000\000\000\002\343\005\000\000\232\000 \000\000\200 \000|\000\000\000\377\377\377\377\356\012\020\000f@\020\000Expanding the Equipment Lists (Dungeon Master Guide)\221\002\000\000=\002\000\000\211\012\020\000\177\015\020\000T\000\000\000 v\200{\004\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\017\000\202\200\001\000\202\203\200\013\000\353\021\000\004\3334izPlayers.hlp\000\200\035\000\211\200\013\000\200\001\000\202\203\202\377\000Expanding the Equipment Lists\000\000\000\000The items listed in the\000 \000\000Player's Handbook\000\000 \000are by no means the only things ever made in the world--or even in a medieval fantasy setting. They are listed because they are the most likely things the characters will need. However, you can certainly add missing or player-requested items to this list.\000\000When you add an item to the lists, first consider the reasonableness of its presence. Given the setting of the AD&D game, adding an M4 Sherman tank as a regular item of equipment is just not a logical, sensible, or wise thing to do.\000\000;\002\000\000\015\002\000\000\356\012\020\000\272\017\020\000.\000\000\000 *\200\033\004\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\203\202\377\000\000Once you decide that a new item is reasonable, you must assign it a cost. Use your judgment. Consider the 