al categories, based on how they are used. The three basic categories are slashing, piercing, and bludgeoning.\000\000\000Slashing weapons\000 \000include swords, axes, and knives. Damage is caused by the combination of weight, muscle, and a good sharp edge.\000\000\000Piercing weapons \000(some swords, spears, pikes, arrows, javelins, etc.) rely on the penetrating power of a single sharp point and much less on the weight of the weapon.\000\000&\002\000\000\355\001\000\000\217\213\030\000\014\300\030\0009\000\000\000 @\200\333\003\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\200\015\000\200\004\000\200\001\000\202\203\202\203\202\377\000\000\000Bludgeoning weapons\000 \000(maces, hammers, and flails) depend almost entirely on the impact caused by weight and muscle.\000\000A few weapons, particularly some of the more exotic pole arms, fall into more than one of these categories. A halberd can be used as a pole-axe (a slashing weapon) or as a short pike (a piercing weapon).\000\000The versatility of these weapons provides the user with a combat advantage in that the mode most favorable to the attacker can be used, depending upon the situation.\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\276\215\030\000\014\300\030\000+\213\030\0009\003\000\000\334\002\000\000\276\215\030\000E\303\030\000]\000\000\000 \210\200\271\005\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\200\015\000\200\004\000\200\001\000\202\203\200\015\000\200\023\000\200\001\000\202\203\353\021\000\004Q\007J&Players.hlp\000\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000\000\000Natural weapons\000 \000can also be classified according to their attack type. Claws are slashing weapons; a bite pierces; a tail-attack bludgeons. The DM must decide which is most appropriate to the creature and method of attack.\000\000\000Armor types\000,\000 in turn, have different qualities. Field plate is more effective, overall, tha