 an attack roll is still required.\000\000The reason is simple: With positive die roll modifiers (for magic, Strength, situation, or whatever), a number greater than 20 can be rolled. Likewise, die roll penalties can push the attack roll below 0.\000\000\246\002\000\000q\002\000\000\204\314\030\000^\001\031\0005\000\000\000 8\200\343\004\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\203\202\200\013\000\200\001\000\202\377\000\000No matter what number a character needs to hit, a roll of 20 is always considered a hit and a roll of 1 is always a miss--unless the DM rules otherwise. Under most circumstances, a natural 20 hits and a natural 1 misses, regardless of any modifiers applied to the die roll.\000\000Thus, even\254\316\030\000^\001\031\000#\314\030\000 if a character's chance to hit a monster is 23 and the character has a -3 penalty applied to the die roll, he might\000be able to score a hit--but only if the die roll is a 20 before any modifiers are applied. Likewise, a character able to hit a monster on a 3 or better, waving a\000 sword +4\000, could still miss if a 1 is rolled on the die.\000\000\256\000\000\000t\000\000\000\254\316\030\000\014\002\031\000:\000\000\000 D\200\350\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\202\202\343*\352$\334\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000\000There are no sure things, good or bad, in the unpredictable chaos of combat situations.\000\000\000\000\000Table of Contents\000\000 \000\000Y\000\000\000(\000\000\000^\001\031\000e\002\031\0001\000\000\000\002\213\006\000\000n\2051\000\331\0052\000\324\000\000\000\377\377\377\377e\002\031\000\227\010\031\000Calculating THAC0 (Dungeon Master Guide)\011\002\000\000\312\001\000\000\014\002\031\000n\004\031\000?\000\000\000 L\200\225\003\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\017\000\202\200\001\000\202\203\202\203\343\353\000\372\271\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000Calculating THAC0\000\000\000\000To make an attack roll, the chara