hile the creature could suffer injury or death falling into a chasm the spell opens under its feet, the magical energy of the spell was directed at the ground, not the creature. Magic resistant creatures are not immune to events that occur as the consequence of spells, only to the direct energy created or released by a spell.\000\000\006\001\000\000\314\000\000\000\026\205 \000\016\211 \000:\000\000\000 B\200\231\001\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\202\343*\352$\334\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000\000Player characters do not normally have magic resistance (though they still get saving throws vs. magical spells and such). This ability is reserved mainly for special monsters.\000\000\000\000Table of Contents\000\000 \000\000i\000\000\0008\000\000\000\010\210 \000w\211 \0001\000\000\000\002\261\014\000\000\215\002A\000\274\202A\000\033\001\000\000\377\377\377\377w\211 \000\235\304 \000Successful Magic Resistance Rolls (Dungeon Master Guide)\212\002\000\000H\002\000\000\016\211 \000\001\214 \000B\000\000\000 R\200\221\004\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\005\000\202\200\001\000\202\203\202\203\200\015\000\200\004\000\200\001\000\200\013\000\200\001\000\202\377\000Successful Magic Resistance Rolls\000\000\000\000A successful magic resistance check can have four different results, depending on the nature of the spell being resisted.\000\000\000Individually Targeted Spells:\000 \000By definition, these spells affect just one creature, and only the targeted creature rolls for magic resistance, if it has any. If a spell of this type is directed at several targets, each target rolls independently of the others. An example of this would be a\000 hold person\000 spell aimed at four creatures, with each creature getting a magic resistance roll, if they have magic resistance.\000\000{\002\000\000D\002\000\000w\211 \000|\216 \0007\000\000\000 <\200\211\004\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\203\200\015\000\200\004\000\200\001\000\202\377\000\000If the magic resistance roll is successful, the spell has no effect on that creature, the spell fails and disappears. If several targets are involved, the spell could still affect others who fail their magic resistance roll.\000\000\000Area-Effect Spells:\000 \000These spells are not targeted on a single creature, but on a point. The spell's effect encompasses everything within a set distance of that point. A successful magic resistance check enables the creature to ignore the effect of the spell. However, the spell is not negated and still applies to all others in the area of effect.\000\000\342\002\000\000\231\002\000\000\001\214 \000j\301 \000I\000\000\000 `\2003\005\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\200\015\000\200\004\000\200\001\000\200\013\000\200\001\000\202\203\200\013\000\200\001\000\200\013\000\200\001\000\202\377\000\000\000In-Place Spells:\000 \000These spells operate continuously in a particular place or on a particular creature, character, or item. \000Protection from evil\000 is one example of this kind of spell.\000\000Magic resistance comes into play only if a creature or item finds himself or itself in the place where the spell is in operati|\216 \000j\301 \000\016\211 \000on. Even then, magic resistance may not come into play. Nothing happens if the spell isn't of a type that affects the character. Thus, a\000 part water\000 spell would not collapse simply because a magic resistant creature walked through the area. A \000protection from evil\000 spell, which could affect the creature, would be susceptible to magic resistance.\000\000\340\002\000\000\241\002\000\000|\216 \000J\304 \000?\000\000\000 L\200C\005\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\203\200\015\000\200\004\000\200\001\000\202\203\200\013\000\200\001\000\202\377\000\000If the DM determines that a magic resistance roll is appropriate, and the roll succeeds, the in-place spell collapses, usually with a dramatic thunderclap and puff of smoke.\000\000\000Permanent Spells:\000 \000Magic resistance is insufficient to destroy a permanent spell. Instead, the spell is negated, within the same guidelines given for in-place spells, for as long as the magic resistant creature is in the area of effect.\000\000Thus, a magic-resistant creature might be able to step through a permanent\000 wall of force\000 enchantment as if it weren't there. However, the wall would spring back into existence as soon as the creature passed through (i.e., no one else can pass through).\000\000S\000\000\000\033\000\000\000j\301 \000\235\304 \0008\000\000\000 @\2006\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\202\202\343*\352$\334\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000\000\000\000\000Table of Contents\000\000 \000\000V\000\000\000%\000\000\000J\304 \000\363\304 \0001\000\000\000\002\262\017\000\0000\006A\000j\002B\000\034\001\000\000\377\377\377\377\363\304 \000\264\003!\000Turning Undead (Dungeon Master Guide)Y\002\000\000&\002\000\000\235\304 \000L\307 \0003\000\000\000 4\200M\004\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\017\000\202\200\001\000\202\203\202\203\202\377\000Turning Undead\000\000\000\000One important, and potentially life-saving, combat ability available to priests and paladins is the ability to turn undead. This is a special power granted by the character's deity. Druids cannot turn undead. However, priests of specific mythoi may be able to at the DM's option.\000\000Through the priest or paladin, the deity manifests a portion of its power, terrifying evil, undead creatures or blasting them right out of existence. However, since the power must be channeled through a mortal vessel, success is not always assured.\000\000\302\003\000\000\210\003\000\000\363\304 \000\016\313 \000:\000\000\000 B\200\021\007\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\343}\247\212\317\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\203\202\377\000\000When encountering undead, 