 dies as a result of poisoning still could have active venom in his system.\000\000Poisons remain effective for 2d6 hours after the death of the victim. If the character is raised during this time, some method must be found to neutralize the poison before the character is restored to life. If this is not done, then after the character rolls the resurrection survival check given in "Raising the Dead," he must immediately roll a successful saving throw vs. poison or suffer all the effects of the poison in his body, as per the normal rules.\000\000\267\000\000\000~\000\000\000R\207$\000\237\212$\0009\000\000\000 B\200\374\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\001\000\203\202\202\343*\352$\334\200\007\000\211\200\001\000\202\377\000\000This may only injure some characters, but it may kill other characters seconds after being raised!\000\000\000\000Table of Contents\000\000 \000\000a\000\000\0000\000\000\000\350\211$\000\000\213$\0001\000\000\000\002\320\004\000\000\210\003I\000i\012I\000<\001\000\000\377\377\377\377\000\213$\000o\217$\000Death from Massive Damage (Dungeon Master Guide)\307\002\000\000\222\002\000\000\237\212$\000\307\215$\0005\000\000\000 8\200%\005\000\200\000\0004\002\212\230\232\206\0300`\200\005\000\202\200\001\000\202\203\202\203\202\203\202\377\000Death from Massive Damage\000\000\000\000In addition to dying when hit points reach 0, a character also runs the risk of dying abruptly when he suffers massive amounts of damage. A character who suffers 50 or more points of damage from a single attack must roll a successful saving throw vs. death, or he dies.\000\000This applies only if the damage was done by a single attack. Multiple attacks totaling 50 points in a single round don't require a saving throw.\000\000For example, a character would be required to make a check if a dragon breathed on him for 72 points of damage. He wouldn't have to do so if eight orcs hit him for a total of 53 points of damage in that round.\000\000\250\001\000\000n